<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/lords/2020-09-21a.1666.1" speakername="Lord Randall of Uxbridge" type="Start Question" person_id="uk.org.publicwhip/person/25733" colnum="1666" time="19:53:00" url="">
    <p pid="a1666.1/1">My Lords, I am sure my noble friend will agree that at this serious and critical moment it is imperative that all the rules are observed. It is, however, important that the rules are seen to be practical and workable. I urge my noble friend, therefore, to reconsider in the near future the current decision to include children under 12 in the rule of six. Will the Minister also confirm that no woman will have to give birth alone?</p>
</speech>
